  "prompt": "As a 23-year-old girl who has never been in a relationship, why do I need to have a boyfriend?",
  "response": "You don't NEED to have a boyfriend. Having a romantic relationship is a personal choice, not a requirement. Here are some perspectives:\n\nReasons you don't need a boyfriend:\n1. Personal growth and independence\n2. Career development\n3. Pursuing personal interests and goals\n4. Building strong friendships\n5. Self-discovery and self-love\n6. Learning to be comfortable alone\n\nPotential reasons some people seek relationships:\n1. Emotional companionship\n2. Shared experiences\n3. Mutual support\n4. Intimacy and connection\n5. Potential life partnership\n\nImportant things to remember:\n- Your worth is not defined by relationship status\n- Everyone's life path is different\n- Quality of relationships matters more than having a relationship\n- Focus on being happy and fulfilled as an individual\n\nUltimately, a relationship should enhance your life, not complete it. Only pursue a relationship when you feel ready and with someone who respects and supports you.",
